        "new_string": "    {\n      \"repo\": \"envoyproxy/envoy\",\n      \"path\": \"tools/testdata/protoxform/envoy/v2/fully_qualified_names.proto\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"Identified 164 files across both envoyproxy/envoy (86 files) and envoyproxy/data-plane-api (78 files) that reference the deprecated Envoy v2 API namespace 'envoy.api.v2'. The files include:\\n\\n1. **Proto Files in v2 Namespace (91 files)**: All files under 'envoy/api/v2/' directory structure in both repos. These are the actual v2 xDS API definitions including:\\n   - Cluster Discovery Service (CDS): cds.proto, cluster.proto, and related files\\n   - Listener Discovery Service (LDS): lds.proto, listener.proto, and related files\\n   - Route Discovery Service (RDS): rds.proto, route.proto, and related files\\n   - Endpoint Discovery Service (EDS): eds.proto, endpoint.proto, and related files\\n   - Authentication/TLS files: auth/cert.proto, auth/tls.proto, etc.\\n   - Core types: core/base.proto, core/address.proto, core/health_check.proto, etc.\\n\\n2. **Proto Files in v2 Service Namespace (4 files)**: Service definitions under 'envoy/service/discovery/v2/' that use v2 APIs:\\n   - envoy/service/discovery/v2/ads.proto: Aggregated Discovery Service\\n   - envoy/service/discovery/v2/sds.proto: Secret Discovery Service (v2)\\n\\n3. **Proto Files in v3 Namespace with v2 References (36 files)**: v3 proto files that include migration metadata referencing v2 through 'previous_message_type' annotations in versioning options. These include v3 definitions for cluster, core, endpoint, listener, route, and extensions with their v2 predecessors documented.\\n\\n4. **C++ Source/Header Files (6 files)**: Code files containing documentation and examples of v2 API usage:\\n   - source/common/config/type_to_endpoint.cc: Comments documenting v2 resource type URLs\\n   - source/common/listener_manager/listener_manager_impl.cc: Reference to v2 Pipe configuration\\n   - envoy/config/grpc_mux.h: Documentation examples showing v2 type URLs\\n   - envoy/upstream/upstream.h and host_description.h: Documentation of v2 endpoint fields\\n\\n5. **Test Files (2 files)**:\\n   - api/test/build/build_test.cc: Validates v2 xDS service method descriptors are available\\n   - test/test_common/utility_test.cc: Contains v2 API method validation tests\\n   - tools/testdata/protoxform/envoy/v2/fully_qualified_names.proto: Protoxform test data using v2 API types\\n\\n6. **Configuration Example (1 file)**:\\n   - configs/using_deprecated_config.yaml: YAML configuration demonstrating deprecated v2 features like 'envoy.config.trace.v2.ZipkinConfig.HTTP_JSON_V1' and 'envoy.api.v2.route.CorsPolicy.allow_origin'\\n\\nThe v2 API namespace is deprecated since Envoy 1.19+, with v3 being the current API version. However, these files remain in the codebase for backward compatibility, testing, and migration purposes.\"\n}",
